                <td height="20" valign="top" class="bodytext">The Process of Wealth Management in BFC Capital consists of:<br />
                  <br />
                  (A) Determining the Asset allocation: <br />
                  On the basis of risk appetite, investment horizon, returns  expectations, present asset-liability positions, expected future inflows and  outflows and other vital informations provided by members.<br />
                  <br />
                  (B) Designing a customized investment plan and suggestion of  Products:<br />
                  This, again, includes:
                  <ol start="1" type="1">
                    <li>Knowing       member&rsquo;s expectations from the product(s)</li>
                    <li>Replacing       member&rsquo;s expectations with realities and putting practical and real       expectations in place</li>
                    <li>Searching       and exploring suitable product(s) from the universe of wealth management solutions       to meet member&rsquo;s objectives.</li>
                    <li>Putting,       in front of members, the product(s) best suited to their requirements.</li>
                  </ol>
                  <p>(C) Periodic Performance review:<br />
                    Includes periodic review of the performance of the  product(s) and recommending amendments, if required.</p>
                  <p>To download wealth management sheet, please click here. <br />
                  </p></td>
